"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence from Norfolk County Council (TIC 064)Norfolk is a largely rural county \nwith significant gaps in its transport infrastructure that disproportionately affect older people, disabled people and those without access to private cars. 28% of \nNorfolk\n’s population is over pensionable age, compared to 19% nationally. There are approxim\nately 180,000 disabled people living in \nNorfolk\n and 38% of households have an income of less than £20,000. Many rural parishes have between 10\n-\n15% of households without access to a car. \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;September 2013\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"